nanoCUL is an example implementation for a Arduino nano and a stand alone CC1101
RF module.
Other arduinos with an ATMega328p and 16 MHz can be used as well.
For more information see http://forum.fhem.de/index.php/topic,24651.0.html


FLASHING FIRMWARE

To update firmware with culfw execute:

	make program

on the a computer which has the avr toolchain installed. This will require some tools installed upfront. 
Use:

	apt-get install make avrdude


to flash the recompiled nanoCUL.hex file.

USING

The culfw stack is available on: /dev/ttyUSBx, where x is a number.
